HEADWORD: Bisulphite
<hw>Bi*sul"phite</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A salt of sulphurous acid in which the base replaces but half the
hydrogen of the acid; an acid sulphite.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bisulphuret</ent>⟦br⟧
